title: Archview Cyclocross Festival
description: Bike Surgeon and team Korte, Hammer Down would like you to join us for this awesome new venue within 5 minutes of downtown St. Louis,MO in Washington Park Il.  Our hope is to build this into a premium venue as we perfect what the course has to offer.
course: Yes, it\'s true! We invite you to join us for cyclocross riding at its finest. Conveniently located less than six miles from downtown St. Louis, the track is nearly 1.5 miles in length and the soil is a mixture of river bottom loam and sand. There are a variety of jumps, from easy to difficult, but all are forgiving. Our goal was to design a track that would challenge all skill levels without sacrificing rider safety. There are no \"do or die\" gap jumps! On scheduled Open Practice days, the track is fully race prepped, safety flaggers are positioned throughout the course, and riders are divided into groups based on bike size and skill level. We\'ve recently completed an elaborate irrigation system designed to maintain optimum track conditions while keeping dust to a minimum. Come out and experience the track everyone is talking about!
directions:
5100 St. Clair Avenue, Washington Park, IL 62203. Take Interstate 64 to Highway 111 South (Exit 6); go right on St. Clair Avenue Track is on the right behind the three large white warehouses.  ATTN: Use exit 6 from hwy 64. . . St. Clair avenue is under construction, and sections of the road are closed. Disregard all instructions from your GPS device or other mapping sources.

title: Melas CX- Basin Racin p/b Garner Cyclery
Miller Chill CX
description: The new Miller Chill Cyclocross race presented by Bloomington Cycle and Fitness will take place on Sunday, December 9 at Miller Park in Bloomington, IL. This is a grassroots effort to bring another cyclocross race opportunity to Central Illinois.  The race is a not-for-profit endeavor that will benefit Bloomington Parks and Recreation.
course: The Miller Chill CX race course has all the classic cyclocross elements: 2 stone bridges, sandy beach crossing, some hills, some pavement, barriers and a small creek crossing.
registration: Registration is through USA Cycling. All races $30 pre-registered, $35 day of registration.  Second race $10. First-time racers only $15 pre-registered and juniors race for free!
notes: See website for prize money distribution and primes.
directions:
Miller Park
1020 South Morris Avenue
Bloomington, IL 61701
